{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/lazyfiltersequence/iterator/enumerated()"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"enumerated()","extendedModule":"Swift","externalID":"s:STsE10enumerateds18EnumeratedSequenceVyxGyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:s18LazyFilterSequenceV8IteratorV","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence/Iterator/enumerated()"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"enumerated","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence","text":"EnumeratedSequence","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A sequence of pairs enumerating the sequence.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example enumerates the characters of the string “Swift” and prints"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each character along with its place in the string."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["for (n, c) in \"Swift\".enumerated() {","    print(\"\\(n): '\\(c)'\")","}","// Prints \"0: 'S'\"","// Prints \"1: 'w'\"","// Prints \"2: 'i'\"","// Prints \"3: 'f'\"","// Prints \"4: 't'\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When you enumerate a collection, the integer part of each pair is a counter","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the enumeration, but is not necessarily the index of the paired value.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"These counters can be used as indices only in instances of zero-based,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"integer-indexed collections, such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Array"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContiguousArray"},{"text":". For","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other collections the counters may be out of range or of the wrong type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to use as an index. To iterate over the elements of a collection with its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indices, use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"zip(_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This example iterates over the indices and elements of a set, building a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"list consisting of indices of names with five or fewer letters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let names: Set = [\"Sofia\", \"Camilla\", \"Martina\", \"Mateo\", \"Nicolás\"]","var shorterIndices: [Set<String>.Index] = []","for (i, name) in zip(names.indices, names) {","    if name.count <= 5 {","        shorterIndices.append(i)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that the "},{"code":"shorterIndices","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" array holds the indices of the shorter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"names in the "},{"code":"names","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" set, you can use those indices to access elements in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the set."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["for i in shorterIndices {","    print(names[i])","}","// Prints \"Sofia\"","// Prints \"Mateo\""],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"name":"Complexity","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"O(1)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a sequence of pairs ("},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"), where "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" represents an element of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the sequence.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence/Iterator"]]},"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence/Iterator":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An iterator over the elements traversed by some base iterator that also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"satisfy a given predicate."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"LazyFilterSequence.Iterator","url":"/documentation/swift/lazyfiltersequence/iterator","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Iterator","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Iterator","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence/Iterator","conformance":{"conformancePrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Conforms when"}],"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Base"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sequence"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"availabilityPrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Available when"}]}},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"type":"topic","title":"Swift","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift","role":"collection","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence/Iterator/enumerated()":{"role":"symbol","title":"enumerated()","url":"/documentation/swift/lazyfiltersequence/iterator/enumerated()","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence/Iterator/enumerated()","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Returns a sequence of pairs (","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"x","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":"), where ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" represents a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" represents an element of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the sequence."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"LazyFilterSequence","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/LazyFilterSequence","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A sequence whose elements consist of the elements of some base"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sequence that also satisfy a given predicate."}],"role":"symbol","title":"LazyFilterSequence","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"LazyFilterSequence","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"/documentation/swift/lazyfiltersequence","type":"topic"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence"}],"abstract":[{"text":"An enumeration of the elements of a sequence or collection.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence","title":"EnumeratedSequence","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift/enumeratedsequence","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EnumeratedSequence","kind":"identifier"}]}}}